@startuml
' @id(SEQ-TEST-PROFILE)
' @ref(USE-TEST-PLAN)
' @desc(SEQ-TEST-PROFILE, "Objective flow for Cycle B across a cycle's life. SETUP (first run): the skill calls Project::detect_test_profile; recommendations are shown and ambiguities surfaced as blocking questions; the operator confirms and the skill writes config.test.layers (no silent default). RUN: at close the skill calls Project::test_plan to get ordered steps, runs each step's command via Bash, and collects exit codes. GATE: it calls Project::evaluate_green_gate(results), which reads config.test.gate — a still-red test blocks close under error, warns under warn. Detection + plan + verdict are deterministic mdd-core; confirmation and execution are skill (Bucket C).")
' Objective sequence for Cycle B: detect-then-confirm the profile, emit
' the deterministic plan, run it at close, and gate on green.
title test profile, plan, green gate (objective)

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev
participant "/mdd-cycle skill" as Skill
participant "Project::detect_test_profile" as Detect
participant "config.yml\ntest.layers/gate" as Cfg
participant "Project::test_plan" as Plan
participant "runner (Bash)" as Bash
participant "Project::evaluate_green_gate" as Gate

== Setup (detect then confirm) ==
Skill -> Detect : detect_test_profile()
Detect --> Skill : recommendations + ambiguities
alt ambiguity
  Skill -> Dev : blocking question (which framework?)
  Dev --> Skill : choice
end
Skill -> Cfg : write confirmed test.layers

== Run + gate (at close, after parity) ==
Skill -> Plan : test_plan()
Plan -> Cfg : test.layers
Plan --> Skill : ordered TestPlanStep[]
loop each step
  Skill -> Bash : run step.command
  Bash --> Skill : exit code
end
Skill -> Gate : evaluate_green_gate(results)
Gate -> Cfg : test.gate
Gate --> Skill : { all_green, still_red, blocking }
alt blocking (gate=error)
  Skill -> Dev : close BLOCKED — tests still red
else warn or all green
  Skill -> Dev : close allowed
end
@enduml
